{"questionId":"33402082","questionHtml":"<p>Find the equation of the oblique asymptote.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><strong>METHOD 1</strong></p>\n<p><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo></math><em> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (A1)</em></strong></p>\n<p>attempts division on <strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></strong><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo></math> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; (A1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>asymptote is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 2</strong></p>\n<p>let asymptote be <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math></p>\n<p><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi><mo>+</mo><mfrac><mi>c</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math><em> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; M1</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mfenced><mrow><mi>a</mi><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></mrow></mfenced><mfenced><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>c</mi></math></strong></p>\n<p>equates coefficients of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi></math>:<em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>a</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>6</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>a</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>b</mi></math></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>b</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfenced><mrow><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfenced></math></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>METHOD 3</strong></p>\n<p><strong><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mo>…</mo></math><em> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; A1</em></strong></p>\n<p><strong><em><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>-</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac></math></em></strong></p>\n<p>attempt to find the limit as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>M1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><munder><mi>lim</mi><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>→</mo><mo>∞</mo></mrow></munder><mfrac><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></mrow><mrow><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></mrow></mfrac><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>2</mn></math><em><strong> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><em><strong>[4 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"33402082","referenceCode":"24N.2.AHL.TZ0.12d","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Find the equation of the oblique asymptote.","paper":"2","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"d","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 4]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.13—Rational functions"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}